    Are tape measures in cm or mm?
    How to Read a Tape Measure in Millimeters. Metric tape measures feature 10 marks to the centimeter. The smallest marks on a tape indicate one millimeter or 1/10th of a centimeter. The large, bold markings on a metric tape measure indicate centimeters.

    Which one is cm on a tape measure?
    If you have a metric tape measure, the numbers should be read like this: The large, numbered markings are centimeters. There is a smaller marking exactly halfway between the centimeters for ease of reading. The smallest markings are millimeters, or one tenth of a centimeter.

    Tape Measure

    Mathematical tool

    Description

    A tape measure or measuring tape is a flexible ruler used to measure length or distance. It consists of a ribbon of cloth, plastic, fibre glass, or metal strip with linear measurement markings. It is a common measuring tool. Wikipedia
    Operation supported: Distance measurement
    Purpose: To serve as a tool for measuring distance
    Made of material option: Plastic, Steel, Metal, Fiberglass, Linen, Invar
    Component: Strip with linear-measurement marking, Ribbon of cloth
    Application: Surveyor
